    <text>
        <body>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Charleston SoCa.</placeName>
                <date>July 20. 1855</date>.</p>
            <p><addressee>Rev. Is. Leeser</addressee>
                <placeName>Philadelphia</placeName>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(4)">Dear Sir—<sic>Inclosed</sic> I<lb/> send you the conclusion of the
                essay, promised to you several months<lb/> ago. Engagements of the most various
                nature, amongst which those attend-<lb/>ant upon <hi rend="underline">going to
                    house-keeping</hi> were not the least,— have, till now,<lb/> prevented me from
                redeeming my promise. I do it now, and hope<lb/> you will excuse me for the long
                delay: Better late than never.</p>
            <p rend="indent(9)">Yours</p>
            <p rend="indent(10)">most friendly &amp; respecting</p>
            <p rend="indent(11)">
                <persName role="author">Dr. M. Mayer</persName>
            </p>
            <p>P. S. Would you, perhaps, have no objection to the publication of a<lb/>
                retrospective view at the history of the Jews of A. M. <date>5615</date>,<lb/> as it
                is published every year in the German papers? The <date>September</date> number<lb/>
                of the Occident being to be published a few days <sic>befor</sic>
                <add>ר"ה</add>, I<lb/> think, such a sketch would not be taken amiss by your<lb/>
                readers. If you wish to have it, I am willing to write it, but<lb/> then you would
                have to allow me some longer time than you usually<lb/> allow, as I should wish to
                carry the history as far down as possible.<lb/> Please let me know at once.    </p>
            <p rend="indent(8)">
                <persName role="author">Dr M Mayer</persName>
            </p>
        </body>
